content.description: Paddle up the low angle start and then head left into the big brown hole... move left across the roof to a steep finish (crux) on the brown rock.  A long sling might help out with rope drag when getting in and out of the hole.  As always, watch out for some loose flakes, though the crux area is pretty solid.
content.protection: 8 bolts to a Mussy Hook anchor
content.location: Starts just left of the toe of the buttress avoiding the obviously scabby rock to the right.

climbs.name: Djangus Unchained
climbs.fa: Rasheed Ali, Alphonso Zapatta, Lisa Zapatta, Vanessa DelToro

content.description: Start on the slab and watch your ankles on the first few moves getting to the first bolt. Trend up and right following bolts.  A couple of minor cruxes are just past mid height.
content.location: Starts just right of Wynona's BBB and wanders up and right from the toe of the south face buttress.
